Newcastle University Overview

Newcastle University is a UK public research university with campuses in Singapore and Malaysia. It is situated in Newcastle upon Tyne, North East England. The university is a red brick institution and a member of the Russell Group, a group of research-intensive universities in the United Kingdom. It is one of ten Russell Group universities to receive a Gold Teaching Excellence Framework (TEF) rating. Our Vision encapsulates our shared sense of purpose. We want to be a people-centered institution that uses academic brilliance, innovation, and creativity to serve individuals, businesses, and society as a whole. Newcastle University exists to enhance education, learning, and research for the benefit of the public. Our goal is to build on this basic mission by providing fresh knowledge and innovative solutions that have a beneficial impact.
To design brighter futures, improve the economy, and support social justice, we want to collaborate with our many external partners.

Newcastle University Admission Requirement

The following requirements must be fulfilled to get admitted to the Newcastle University

  • International students are considered on a case-by-case basis. There can be some additional requirements, depending on the program you are applying to.
  • Students are required to submit their original transcripts from their last attended academic institutions. If they are not in English, then submit the translated copies of the same along with the originals.
  • Applicants must be 18 years old at the time of the beginning of the course.
  • You need to submit your English language proficiency test scores if you are coming from a non-English speaking country.

Newcastle University Students

As one of the world’s top research universities, Northeastern has the resources, global connections, and international mindset to help you succeed in your studies and career no matter where they take you.

Our low drop-out rates and high satisfaction score in the National Student Survey are testament to the excellent support you can expect at Newcastle. All of our support services are free of charge and available to all students.

We offer a range of services to ensure that you can reach your full potential. Our dedicated Student Services building, King's Gate, is in the heart of campus. Our Student Advice Centre is in the Students' Union.
Our Student Services team offers help, advice and support on a wide range of issues. King's Gate is open every weekday. If you have a general enquiry, you can contact us via our online enquiries form.
Your personal tutor will support you throughout your time at Newcastle. They can offer practical guidance on a wide range of academic and non-academic issues. You can also seek support from a student mentor; a fellow student on your degree who has been trained to support incoming students.
